Supersport United and Warriors defender Onismor Bhasera is reported to have escaped death by a whisker after his BMW was involved in a serious accident along Mutare-Masvingo road on Monday.The report suggest that Bhasera was traveling to his South African base when the vehicle he was traveling in hit a killer pothole and the player lost control before the vehicle veered off the road and overturned a couple of times before landing on its back.&nbsp;No official comment has so far been obtained from the victim, but it is understood that the car is now beyond repair but he escaped unscathed.&nbsp;